OL,3,CStove manufacturer fined #200,000
OL,4,Cafter employee loses leg
OL,6,FA manufacturer of wood-burning stoves
OL,7,Fon the Isle of Wight has been fined
OL,8,F#200,000 after an employee had his leg
OL,9,Fcrushed when heavy metal sheets fell
OL,10,Fon him.
OL,12,FThe man was working for A J Wells &
OL,13,FSons Ltd in Newport, when the incident
OL,14,Fhappened on 15 August 2023.
OL,16,FHe had been moving a trolley loaded
OL,17,Fwith approximately 30 pieces of sheet
OL,18,Fmetal, each weighing more than 20kg,
OL,19,Fwhen it toppled over and fell onto his
OL,20,Flegs.
