OL,3,CStove manufacturer fined #200,000
OL,4,Cafter employee loses leg
OL,6,FHis lower right leg was later
OL,7,Famputated as a result of the injuries
OL,8,Fhe sustained.
OL,10,FAn investigation by the Health and
OL,11,FSafety Executive (HSE) found that the
OL,12,Fwork was not being carried out safely.
OL,14,FFailures included the use of a trolley
OL,15,Fthat was not suitable for transporting
OL,16,Fsuch loads, unclear routes throughout
OL,17,Fthe factory for moving trolleys, and
OL,18,Finadequate training for employees in
OL,19,Fthe safe movement of heavy materials.
